==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phallus
<hw>Phal"lus</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧l"l⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Phalli</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a
phallus (in sense 1), Gr. <grk>fallo`s</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The emblem of the generative power in nature, carried in procession
in the Bacchic orgies, or worshiped in various ways.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The penis or clitoris, or the
embryonic or primitive organ from which either may be derived.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of fungi which have a
fetid and disgusting odor; the stinkhorn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1075 --></p>

<p><ent>Phanar</ent>⟦br⟧
